# Shared context adapter

This is a fictional template. Merge it into the appropriate Codex instruction file; do not copy it over an existing file without review.

## Shared root

The private shared context root is `your_private_shared_root`.

Start with the current user request and repository-local `AGENTS.md` guidance. Access the shared root only when the task needs cross-session or personal context.

## Retrieval ladder

1. Read `your_private_shared_root/TODAY.md` when current focus or handoff state is relevant.
2. Read `your_private_shared_root/QUICK_CONTEXT.md` when system orientation is relevant.
3. Check `your_private_shared_root/memory/MEMORY.md`, then open only the topic file that owns the subject.
4. If the hot index misses, search the shared memory and vault narrowly.
5. Follow at most one relevant note link before reassessing.

Do not bulk-read the memory or vault. Do not assume that Claude Code hooks, permissions, plugins, or `CLAUDE.md` apply to Codex.

## Durable saves

When the user explicitly asks to remember, recap, or hand off work:

- update an existing owner note before creating a new one;
- keep `MEMORY.md` concise and use it as an index;
- put long-form project decisions in the vault;
- append one concise entry to `vault/log.md` for a meaningful vault change;
- keep credentials and raw transcripts out of all shared stores.

## Governance

Propose changes to global instructions, shared skills, hooks, permissions, and memory conventions before applying them. Verify that any installed component actually loads and affects the intended behavior.
